Enum Constant Detail

DEFAULTIO

public static final AoScanOption DEFAULTIO
Transfers D/A data based on the the board type and sampling speed.

SINGLEIO

public static final AoScanOption SINGLEIO
Transfers one packet of data at a time. Each packet can contain multiple data samples, but only one sample from each channel. The sample rate is system dependent.

BLOCKIO

public static final AoScanOption BLOCKIO
Transfers D/A data in blocks. Not recommended for slow acquisition rates, as the operation status is not available until one packet of data is collected (typically 512 samples).

CONTINUOUS

public static final AoScanOption CONTINUOUS
Scans data in an endless loop. Once the required number of samples are acquired, the buffer is reset and the operation begins again. Call stopBackground to stop the operation.

EXTCLOCK

public static final AoScanOption EXTCLOCK
Data conversions are paced by an external clock signal. Each conversion is triggered on the appropriate edge of the clock input signal.

The rate parameter is ignored. The sampling rate is dependent on the clock signal. The transfer mode which allows the maximum conversion rate is used, unless otherwise specified.

BURSTMODE

public static final AoScanOption BURSTMODE
Enables burst mode sampling, minimizing the channel skew. Scans from lowChan to highChan are clocked at the maximum D/A rate between samples to minimize channel to channel skew. Scans are initiated at the rate specified by the rate parameter.

BurstMode is not recommended for use with the SINGLEIO option. If this combination is used, set the sample count as low as possible – preferably to the number of channels in the scan – to avoid a data overrun.

EXTTRIGGER

public static final AoScanOption EXTTRIGGER
Sampling begins when a trigger condition is met. The trigger condition is programmable on some devices; refer to setTrigger.

RETRIGGER

public static final AoScanOption RETRIGGER
Re-arms the trigger after a trigger event is performed. The scan begins when a trigger event occurs. When the scan completes, the trigger is re-armed to acquire the next batch of data. Use with the Continuous option to continue arming the trigger until StopBackground is called.

Use the SetTrigger retriggerCount parameter to specify the number of samples to acquire with each trigger event. If you specify a trigger count that is either zero or greater than the value of the aOutScan samplesPerChan parameter, the trigger count is set to the value of samplesPerChan.

Specify the Continuous option with the trigger count set to zero to fill the buffer with samplesPerChan samples, re-arm the trigger, and refill the buffer upon the next trigger.

NOCALIBRATEDATA

public static final AoScanOption NOCALIBRATEDATA
Turns off real-time software calibration for devices that are software calibrated.

Calibration factors are applied to the data on a sample by sample basis as acquired.
